  "body": "We have seen the following [patterns](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/master/beacon-chain/core/validators/validator.go#L475-L479) all over the repo with our proto objects. It'd be nice to have a generalized hashing function which can take in any object that fulfills the proto interface and use that to hash the object. This function should reside in [hashutils](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/tree/master/shared/hashutil) and should abstract the marshaling and then hashing similarly to the following:\r\n```go\r\n\r\nfunc HashProto(object proto.Message) ([32]byte,error) {\r\n marshalledObj := proto.Marshal(object)\r\n return Hash(marshalledObj)\r\n}\r\n```",
