    "body": "hey @aunyks , yes the idea is that we would not need separate hashing functions for different proto objects. So for example over here: \r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/master/beacon-chain/core/blocks/block.go#L18\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/master/beacon-chain/core/state/state.go#L142\r\n\r\nwe wouldn't need the two above functions, so a generalized hashing function would look like:\r\nthis:\r\n\r\n`func HashProto(object proto.Message) ([32]byte,error) `\r\n\r\nA PR would replace all usages of the specific hash functions with the generalized functions.\r\n\r\nI have changed the above code example to be more accurate.",
